content.description: Starting on a good right edge and less good left edge, head up passing another good edge to a not-as-positive top (footwork helps!)Problem #412 in Rock Jock's Guide, rated P2.
content.location: Right side of the face on the small wall set back on far right end of Main Wall.

content.description: Short but fun, wish it was taller! Climb up the scoop past two thin cracks (left end of sideways "Y" crack) and on to a fun high step/mantle move over the lip.Problem #411 in Rock Jock's Guide, rated P1.
content.location: Left side of the face on the small wall set back on far right end of Main Wall.

content.description: Sit start under the bulge at the end of the wall and do a couple quick moves on edges and small pockets until standing on the low angle rock. Follow the ramp to the top of the wall, or just finish off right whenever and call it good.Problem #410 in Rock Jock's Guide, rated P3.
content.protection: Pad, maybe a second to cover the rock to the right depending on the holds you use.
content.location: Far right end of the wall, left of a small boulder.

content.description: Sit start at the right end of an angled crack. Head left using the crack, and moreso the positive pockets below the crack, to the left-most large pocket. From there, head straight up and enjoy the slightly more technical topout between the large flake to the left and a lone 2 finger pocket on the lower angle section... it's still a ways to go!Problem #409 in Rock Jock's Guide, rated P2.
content.location: Far right end of the wall, can't miss it.

content.description:
A long wall with a shorter wall set back at each end of it with mostly 20+ foot tall problems. Most have TR bolts available. Problems range from P1 to P10, plenty of harder problems to be had. 

  This wall is also North/Northwest facing, so a good spot on warmer days.
